title: Is Turkey Trying to Sabotage Massive New Israel-Cyprus-Greece EastMed Gas Deal?
text:
Turkey sees that its old adversaries, Greece and Cyprus, and its new adversaries, Israel and Egypt, are forming a maritime axis that is blocking it.

Soner Cagaptay, director of the Turkish Research Program at the Washington Institute for Near East Policy, told JNS.Tensions are reaching a new high in the eastern Mediterranean region after the Turkey’s parliament approved a measure to deploy Turkish troops to Libya to support the U.N.-backed government there.
